        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 2:13PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 213 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Forestville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Harbor Beach, Helena, Ruth, White Rock, and Parisville.

People attending Harbor Beach  should seek safe shelter immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
